9a. I used both a gradient, and many instances of shadows to make elements on my page pop. Textwise I included both a text shadow and a gradient on my main header title.
9b. I pretty much used relative units and the clamp() function everywhere in my CSS. Two such examples are:
h1 { font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 6vw, 2.5rem); }
section > h2 { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); }

12. b,c,a
    (b) I used many instances of box shadow, using its effects on the navigation bar, skill blocks, project cards, etc. (c) For hover on project cards, and skill cards I give it a lift effect with transforming it up a bit. I also use transforms to create the animation for the opening and closing of the hamburger navigation bar. (a) I use a CSS gradient on the main title for the page.

